author: wcax.com
title: Propane leak cleared in Auburn
text:
AUBURN, N.H. (AP) - The police department in Auburn says a propane leak has been cleared up, and no one was hurt.
Crews from Auburn, Manchester and Derry responded to the leak on Bypass 28 early Friday afternoon. The road was closed near Priscilla Lane and some evacuations were reported.
Police said the leak was cleared and Bypass 28 was reopened at about 1:30 p.m.
